    <para id="id12290273">3/ List of simple properties</para>
    <para id="id12290277">Some of the important properties are summarized here; a more complete list is appended.</para>
    <figure id="id12290289">
      <media id="id19837190" alt=""><image src="../../media/graphics1-b389.png" mime-type="image/png" height="208" width="600"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id12290316">a/ Properties — linearity</para>
    <para id="id12290321">Most proofs of Fourier transform properties are simple. </para>
    <para id="id12290333"><m:math>
		<m:mrow>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:msub>
					<m:mi>ax</m:mi>
					<m:mn>1</m:mn>
				</m:msub>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mo>(</m:mo>
					<m:mi>t</m:mi>
					<m:mo>)</m:mo>
				</m:mrow>
			</m:mrow>
			<m:mo>+</m:mo>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:msub>
					<m:mi>bx</m:mi>
					<m:mn>2</m:mn>
				</m:msub>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mo>(</m:mo>
					<m:mi>t</m:mi>
					<m:mo>)</m:mo>
				</m:mrow>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mover>
					<m:mrow>
						<m:mtext>
						</m:mtext>
						<m:mrow>
							<m:mo>⟺</m:mo>
							<m:mtext>
							</m:mtext>
						</m:mrow>
					</m:mrow>
					<m:mi>F</m:mi>
				</m:mover>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:msub>
					<m:mi>aX</m:mi>
					<m:mn>1</m:mn>
				</m:msub>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mo>(</m:mo>
					<m:mi>f</m:mi>
					<m:mo>)</m:mo>
				</m:mrow>
			</m:mrow>
			<m:mo>+</m:mo>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:msub>
					<m:mi>bX</m:mi>
					<m:mn>2</m:mn>
				</m:msub>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mo>(</m:mo>
					<m:mi>f</m:mi>
					<m:mo>)</m:mo>
