			</m:mrow>
		</m:mrow>
	</m:math></para>
    <para id="id12290362">The proof follows from the definition of the Fourier transform as a definite integral.</para>
    <para id="id12290368"><m:math>
		<m:mrow>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:mi>X</m:mi>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mo>(</m:mo>
					<m:mi>f</m:mi>
					<m:mo>)</m:mo>
				</m:mrow>
			</m:mrow>
			<m:mo>=</m:mo>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:msubsup>
					<m:mo>∫</m:mo>
					<m:mrow>
						<m:mo>-</m:mo>
