    <para id="id11522406">Two-minute miniquiz problem</para>
    <para id="id11522410">Problem 17-1 — Step with a dc offset</para>
    <para id="id11522415">Find the Fourier transform of x(t).</para>
    <figure id="id12282079">
      <media id="id20487945" alt=""><image src="../../media/l6f20.png" mime-type="image/png" height="108" width="171"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id12282103">Solution</para>
    <para id="id12282107">We can represent x(t) as</para>
    <para id="id12282131">x(t) = 3/2 + (1/2)sgn(t).</para>
    <para id="id12282184">Hence,</para>
    <para id="id12282191"><m:math>
		<m:mrow>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:mi>X</m:mi>
				<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mo>(</m:mo>
					<m:mi>f</m:mi>
					<m:mo>)</m:mo>
				</m:mrow>
			</m:mrow>
			<m:mo>=</m:mo>
			<m:mrow>
				<m:mrow>
					<m:mrow>
						<m:mo>(</m:mo>
						<m:mrow>
							<m:mn>3</m:mn>
							<m:mo>/</m:mo>
							<m:mn>2</m:mn>
						</m:mrow>
						<m:mo>)</m:mo>
					</m:mrow>
					<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
					<m:mi>δ</m:mi>
					<m:mo>⁢</m:mo>
					<m:mrow>
						<m:mo>(</m:mo>
						<m:mi>f</m:mi>
						<m:mo>)</m:mo>
					</m:mrow>
				</m:mrow>
				<m:mo>+</m:mo>
				<m:mfrac>
					<m:mn>1</m:mn>
					<m:mi>j2πf</m:mi>
				</m:mfrac>
			</m:mrow>
		</m:mrow>
	</m:math></para>
    <para id="id12282221">9/ Causal cosinusoidal time function</para>
    <para id="id12282225">A causal cosinusoid is a cosinusoid that starts at t = 0,</para>
    <para id="id12282244"><m:math>
		<m:mrow>
			<m:mrow>
