    </figure>
    <para id="id11738534">Note that as T decreases x(t) becomes tall and narrow and X(f) gets broader in frequency. Interpreted as generalized functions, x(t) → δ(t) and X(f) → 1.</para>
    <para id="id11799056">11/ Triangular pulse</para>
    <para id="id11799060">A triangular pulse is obtained by convolving a rectangular pulse with itself.</para>
    <figure id="id11799072">
      <media id="id20723146" alt=""><image src="../../media/l6f23.png" mime-type="image/png" height="195" width="520"/></media>
    </figure>
    <para id="id11799095">Since xT (t)=xR(t)*xR(t), the triangular pulse has the transform</para>
    <para id="id11799173"><m:math>
		<m:mrow>
